# Version Management

When implementing new features or making changes to this Chrome extension, update the version number in `manifest.json` following semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH).

## When to Bump

| Change Type | Version Bump | Examples |
|-------------|--------------|----------|
| Breaking changes | MAJOR (X.0.0) | Removing features, changing core behavior incompatibly |
| New features | MINOR (x.X.0) | Adding new functionality, new options, UI enhancements |
| Bug fixes, refactors | PATCH (x.x.X) | Fixing bugs, code cleanup, performance improvements |

## Guidelines

- **Always bump** when implementing user-requested features or fixes
- **Skip bumping** for documentation-only changes or rule file updates
- **Reset lower numbers** when bumping higher ones (e.g., 1.2.3 â†’ 2.0.0)

## Example

```json
// Before adding a new feature
"version": "1.0.0"

// After adding a new feature
"version": "1.1.0"
```
